siness in more than  countries citigroup has  employees although it had  employees at its height before the financial crisis of  citigroup suffered huge losses during the financial crisis of  and was rescued in november  in a massive stimulus package by the us government contents  current operations  history  citicorp –  travelers group –  ownership of salomon brothers –  merger of citicorp and travelers –  spinoff of travelers   subprime mortgage crisis   collapse  us government intervention   creation of citi holdings   sale of morgan stanley smith barney   return to profitability denationalization   expansion of retail banking operations   expansion of credit card operations   federal reserve stress tests –  spinoff of napier park global capital   downsizing of consumer banking unit    onwards  offices  new york city  naming rights to citi field  chicago  regulatory action lawsuits and arbitration  enron worldcom and global crossing bankruptcies  criticism  alleged money laundering by raul salinas  conflicts of interest on investment research  citigroup proprietary government bond trading scandal of   plutonomy report  tarp funding  terra securities scandal  allegations of theft from customer accounts  potential restructuring and liquidation by regulators  shareholder rejection of executive compensation plan  accusations of futures market manipulation  communications  lobbying  public and governmental relations  see also  references  further reading  external links current operationsedit a citi private bank office citigroup is the holding company for the following divisions citigroup global markets inc citigroup global markets limited uk and citigroup global markets japan  broker dealers including one of  primary dealers in united states treasury securities citis institutional clients group icg offers investment and corporate banking services and products for companies governments institutions and ultra highnetworth investors icg consists of the following five main divisions capital markets origination is focused on the capitalraising needs such as public offerings private placements and special purpose acquisition companies corporate  investment banking provides strategic and financing products and advisory services to multinational and local corporations financial institutions governments and privately held businesses in more than  countries it also provides client services such as mergers  acquisitions advice and underwriting of initial public offerings markets  securities services includes investor services and direct custody and clearing hedge fund and private equity servicing and issuer businesses it provides financial products through underwriting sales  trading of a range of investment assets products offered include servicing of equities commodities credit futures foreign exchange fx emerging markets g rates municipals prime financebrokerage services and securitized markets such as collateralized debt obligations and mortgagebacked securities its citi research team provides equity and fixed income research company sector economic and geographic market analysis and productspecific analysis for citis individual and institutional clients its flagship research reports include the following portfolio strategist bond market roundup us economics weekly international market roundup global economic outlook  strategy and the global equity strategist citi private bank advises professional investors ultra highnetworth individuals and families and lawyers throughout the world it uses an open architecture network of more than  private bankers and investment professionals across  countries and jurisdictions to provide clients access to global investment opportunities it has over  billion in assets under management the minimum net worth requirement is  million in liquid assets and is waived for only law firm groups and other clients under special circumstances citibank private bank treasury and trade solutions tts provides cash ma